# Security Standards

## Authentication
- Passwords: BCrypt only, work factor ≥ 12 — never MD5, SHA-1, or plain SHA-256
- JWT access tokens: 15-minute expiry (`JWT_EXPIRY_MS=900000`)
- JWT refresh tokens: 7-day expiry, stored server-side (revocable)
- JWT secret: minimum 256-bit (32 bytes), from environment variable ONLY
- OAuth2: use PKCE flow — never implicit grant
- Never log tokens, passwords, or PII at any log level

## API Security
- All endpoints require authentication unless explicitly public
- Use `@PreAuthorize` for role-based access — don't check roles in service layer
- Rate limiting: add `bucket4j` or Spring's rate limiting for `/api/v1/auth/**`
- CORS: restrict `allowedOrigins` to known domains — never use `*` in production
- Input validation: use `@Valid` + Bean Validation on ALL request DTOs

## Secrets Management
- Zero secrets in source code — use environment variables or a secrets manager
- `.env` is in `.gitignore` — only `.env.example` goes to git
- In production: use AWS SSM Parameter Store, HashiCorp Vault, or Railway secrets
- Rotate JWT secrets and OAuth credentials every 90 days

## OWASP Top 10 Checklist
- A01 Broken Access Control: `@PreAuthorize` on every protected endpoint
- A02 Cryptographic Failures: BCrypt for passwords, AES-256 for token encryption at rest
- A03 Injection: JPA parameterized queries only — no string concatenation in queries
- A05 Security Misconfiguration: review `application-prod.properties` before every deploy
- A06 Vulnerable Components: OWASP dependency check runs in CI (fails on CVSS ≥ 9)
- A07 Auth Failures: lockout after 5 failed login attempts (future: add `bucket4j`)
- A09 Logging: structured logging, never log sensitive data, audit auth events

## Dependency Management
- Run `mvn dependency:check` before merging to main
- Dependabot alerts must be resolved within 7 days for HIGH, 24h for CRITICAL
- Never disable OWASP check in CI — fix the vulnerability instead

## Docker Security
- Never run containers as root — use `USER 1000:1000` in Dockerfiles
- Use minimal base images (Alpine, distroless)
- Scan images with `docker scout` or Trivy before pushing to registry
- Secrets: use Docker secrets or environment injection — never in Dockerfile `ENV`
